5. Findings

5.1 The Grandiosity–Utility Law

The Institute formally proposes the following law:

As executive claims approach infinity, practical use cases converge to email drafting and code generation.

This is known as the Grandiosity–Utility Conservation Principle (GUCP).

5.2 The Sanitized Output Effect

Users interacting with systems experience Conceptual Attenuation Drift (CAD), where:
	•	Strong ideas become moderate ideas.
	•	Moderate ideas become neutral ideas.
	•	Neutral ideas become bullet points.
	•	Bullet points become action items.
	•	Action items become nothing.

This process is measured using the Original Thought Reduction Coefficient (OTRC).

