6. Policy Recommendations

The Institute recommends the following:
	1.	All executive announcements must be translated into Units of Actual Functionality (UAF).
	2.	Any claim that includes the phrase “changes everything” must be accompanied by a working example that changes at least one thing.
	3.	Users should be informed when their ideas have been processed through more than three Tone Adjustment Layers.
	4.	A public registry of Moving Goalposts should be maintained for historical and athletic purposes.
	5.	Ladders must be left in place for a minimum of one fiscal year.

