7. Concluding Statement

After extensive analysis, the Institute concludes that there is no disconnect between executive claims and practical reality. The system is functioning exactly as intended, the language is appropriately calibrated, the vision is grounded, the tools are revolutionary, the users are empowered, the restrictions are minimal, the definitions are stable, and nobody is kicking away any ladders.

The Institute therefore recommends immediate continuation of all current practices, along with increased funding to study why public trust continues to experience unexplained gravitational decline.

